text: Tohmajärvi is a municipality in North Karelia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 4,066 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Joensuu, Kitee and Rääkkylä. Since 2005, Värtsilä became a part of Tohmajärvi. Tohmajärvi was founded in 1869. == Other websites == * Municipality of Tohmajärvi – Official website Category:Municipalities of North Karelia Category:1869 establishments in Europe Category:1860s establishments in Finland
